My meme

There are 9 images in my meme. One white image blank in each corner and center. There are different image in middle of top, both sides and bottom This is the first idea in my mind when I see the instruction to create a new image.

p{font-size: 25px;
  color: #ff3406
  }

code:

#import magick packet
library(magick)

#Assign each images to a specific object
image1 <- image_read("image1.png") %>% 
  image_scale(200)

image2 <- image_read("image2.png") %>% 
  image_scale(200)

image3 <- image_read("image3.png") %>% 
  image_scale(200)

image4 <- image_read("image4.png") %>% 
  image_scale(200)

#Create an image blank to show the direction
background_left_top <- image_blank(width = 200, height = 100, color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Left top", gravity = "center")

background_left_bot <- image_blank(width = 200, height = 100, color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Left bot", gravity = "center")

background_right_top <- image_blank(width = 200, height = 100, color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Right top", gravity = "center")

background_right_bot <- image_blank(width = 200, height = 100, color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Right bot", gravity = "center")

background_mid <- image_blank(width = 200, height = 100, color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Mid", gravity = "center")


#append each image and blank to for a row of the whole image
top_row <- c(background_left_top, image1, background_right_top) %>%
  image_append()

mid_row <- c(image2, background_mid, image3) %>%
  image_append()

bot_row <- c(background_left_bot, image4, background_right_bot) %>%
  image_append()


#append all rows as an final image
meme <- c(top_row, mid_row, bot_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)
meme %>% image_write("my_meme.png")
meme

My animated GIF

p{font-size: 25px;
  color: #ff5408
  }

Based on the previous task. I created this image by myself. I want to add some animation on it. Let each image loops and never stops.

code:

#import magick packet
library(magick)

#Assign each images to a specific object
image1 <- image_read("image1.png") %>% 
  image_scale(200)

image2 <- image_read("image2.png") %>% 
  image_scale(200)

image3 <- image_read("image3.png") %>% 
  image_scale(200)

image4 <- image_read("image4.png") %>% 
  image_scale(200)

#Create an image blank to show the direction
background_left_top <- image_blank(width = 200, height = 100, color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Left top", gravity = "center")

background_left_bot <- image_blank(width = 200, height = 100, color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Left bot", gravity = "center")

background_right_top <- image_blank(width = 200, height = 100, color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Right top", gravity = "center")

background_right_bot <- image_blank(width = 200, height = 100, color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Right bot", gravity = "center")

background_mid <- image_blank(width = 200, height = 100, color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Mid", gravity = "center")


#append each image and blank to for a row of the whole image
top_row1 <- c(background_left_top, image1, background_right_top) %>%
  image_append()

mid_row1 <- c(image2, background_mid, image3) %>%
  image_append()

bot_row1 <- c(background_left_bot, image4, background_right_bot) %>%
  image_append()


top_row2 <- c(image2, background_left_top, image1) %>%
  image_append()

mid_row2 <- c(background_left_bot, background_mid, background_right_top) %>%
  image_append()

bot_row2 <- c(image4, background_right_bot, image3) %>%
  image_append()


top_row3 <- c(background_left_bot, image2, background_left_top) %>%
  image_append()

mid_row3 <- c(image4, background_mid, image1) %>%
  image_append()

bot_row3 <- c(background_right_bot, image3, background_right_top) %>%
  image_append()


top_row4 <- c(image4, background_left_bot, image2) %>%
  image_append()

mid_row4 <- c(background_right_bot, background_mid, background_left_top) %>%
  image_append()

bot_row4 <- c(image3, background_right_top, image1) %>%
  image_append()


top_row5 <- c(background_right_bot, image4, background_left_bot) %>%
  image_append()

mid_row5 <- c(image3, background_mid, image2) %>%
  image_append()

bot_row5 <- c(background_right_bot, image1, background_left_top) %>%
  image_append()


top_row6 <- c(image3, background_right_bot, image4) %>%
  image_append()

mid_row6 <- c(background_right_top, background_mid, background_left_bot) %>%
  image_append()

bot_row6 <- c(image1, background_left_top, image2) %>%
  image_append()


top_row7 <- c(background_right_top, image3, background_right_bot) %>%
  image_append()

mid_row7 <- c(image1, background_mid, image4) %>%
  image_append()

bot_row7 <- c(background_left_bot, image2, background_left_bot) %>%
  image_append()


top_row8 <- c(image1, background_right_top, image3) %>%
  image_append()

mid_row8 <- c(background_left_top, background_mid, background_right_bot) %>%
  image_append()

bot_row8 <- c(image2, background_left_bot, image4) %>%
  image_append()


#append all rows as an final image
meme1 <- c(top_row1, mid_row1, bot_row1) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)


meme2 <- c(top_row2, mid_row2, bot_row2) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)


meme3 <- c(top_row3, mid_row3, bot_row3) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)


meme4 <- c(top_row4, mid_row4, bot_row4) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)


meme5 <- c(top_row5, mid_row5, bot_row5) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)


meme6 <- c(top_row6, mid_row6, bot_row6) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)


meme7 <- c(top_row7, mid_row7, bot_row7) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

  
meme8 <- c(top_row8, mid_row8, bot_row8) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)


memes <- c(meme1, meme2, meme3, meme4, meme5, meme6, meme7, meme8)

animation <- image_animate(memes, fps = 1)
animation %>% image_write("my_animation.gif")
animation
